    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I grew up accustomed to bitterness. I come from the land of radicchio, and when in season, its bitter presence is constant – a staple vegetable grown in each and every patch. My grandmother was a forager of wild herbs, the bitter ones, and she would cook them and then season them with the liquified fat from the cooked fresh salame. Turns out, I grew craving bitter food much more than sweet. In fact, I don&#39;t like sweet, but the sweetness of bitter leaves cooked in butter, that I like. Thank you for this sweet memories with us, like you did in A Homemade Life. Fell better soon, Molly! x</p>
