    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love love love when you posted anything that cooks for two hours (that cabbage is always in the oven or on deck around here). And I trust anything you have to say about endive! I&#39;d never had them anyway but reluctantly, raw with tapenade on a party platter, until your cream braised recipe a hundred years ago (let me check &#8230; crikey, almost nine!). I remember making that a couple months later, for a friend, in France, and marveling over how cheap they were there in comparison to the Union Square Whole Foods, where they were something like $12/lb. Mmmm. Memories. I&#39;m going to make this version soon.</p>
    </div>

