    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My dad has been gone for a third of my life as well, and he died in December, too. </p>
<p>He adored food. He and a friend, the daughter of a professional French chef, would battle over who made the best Thanksgiving dinner, full of unnatural (to a child) dishes like creamed celery root and wild rice with roasted chestnuts. </p>
<p>He was famous for big holiday brunches, his pies, and rolls. The holidays are not the same. We make his food and toast to him, but it&#39;s not the same.</p>
    </div>

